</li>
<li id="cite_note-odnb-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-odnb_4-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">
Glanmor Williams, 'Houghton, Adam (d. 1389)', in <i><a href="/wiki/Oxford_Dictionary_of_National_Biography" class="mw-redirect" title="Oxford Dictionary of National Biography">Oxford Dictionary of National Biography</a></i> (Oxford University Press, 2004), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/article/13863,">online edition</a>, May 2008 (subscription required), accessed 4 December 2010</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-chancery-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-chancery_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-chancery_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-chancery_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-chancery_5-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-chancery_5-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Bertie Wilkinson, <i>The Chancery under Edward III</i> (1929), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=mRkNAQAAIAAJ&amp;pg=PA142">p. 142</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">W. H. Bliss, ed., <i>Calendar of Papal Registers, Petitions</i>, vol. 1 for 1342–1419 (1896), p. 106; <i>Calendar of Papal Registers, Letters</i>, vol. 3, p. 238</span>
</li>
